Ok - I was Dave Duffner's girl aka Silicon Falcon.  CFN was the first time I was ever introduced to a computer or chatting or anything.  I think I spent 18 hours a day on that thing.  We moved away in 92 I think.  I have since married, divorced, remarried - a couple of times... since those long ago times.
 
I now live in Ashtabula county.  Have twin almost 10 year old daughters.  Been married now for 5 years.  Own a house out here in the middle of no where and love it. Which reminds me,  I have to admit I do miss the close community it use to be before the big web explosion.  The internet is great but the neat thing about the IRC was that we were not that far apart and could get together for those fun picnics!
 
I don't mind the pic so much, it scares me - my god was I young - and thin...  LOL  And crazy. 
 
I would be up for a picnic sure!  That would be great - however - can we at least have it on the East side of Cleveland.  LOL  It's a heck of a drive out that way these days.  LOL
 
Shannon
